{"id":4562,"date":"2022-08-26T05:53:49","date_gmt":"2022-08-26T05:53:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/kjoumaa.com\/klima\/?post_type=dt_portfolio&#038;p=4562"},"modified":"2024-12-23T09:14:51","modified_gmt":"2024-12-23T09:14:51","slug":"smoke-control-damper","status":"publish","type":"dt_portfolio","link":"https:\/\/klimacontra.com\/products\/smoke-control-damper\/","title":{"rendered":"Smoke Control Damper"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;4563&#8243; img_size=&#8221;450&#215;350&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><u>Description:<\/u><\/strong><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The smoke control dampers are intended to be installed in smoke and heat control systems, acting as a protection layer against the spreading of fire, temperature and smoke.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">During the normal operation of the system, the flap of the damper is in the open or closed position. In case of fire, the actuating system opens the dampers which operates in the fire detection zone (dampers in other zones move to the closed position). These dampers are non-symmetrical, intended for vertical installation (in walls). They can be also installed in rigid building barriers.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The smoke control damper is composed of two bodies made of galvanized steel, which are separated with insulating dividers made of 40 mm thick, fire-resistant material. Inside the damper, the flap which movement in closed position is limited with a stop bar. The axles of flap cooperate with slide bearing built in the insulating dividers. The closing of the flap is realized by the system of the flexible connectors.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The smoke control damper is based on one united body. The damper is optionally provided with two inspection holes at the top and the bottom., which makes it not necessary to install inspection covers in the duct before the damper, for making periodic inspection and testing. There is also no need to specify the service side.<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><u>Test and certification:<\/u><\/strong><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The damper is constructed, manufactured and tested in accordance with the standards<strong><u> PN-EN 12101-8<\/u><\/strong> and <strong><u>PN-EN 13501-4.<\/u><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The sensitivity of the damper is confirmed by tests in accordance with the standards<strong> <u>PN-EN 1366-2<\/u> <\/strong>and<strong> <u>PN-EN 1366-10.<\/u><\/strong><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;4563&#8243; img_size=&#8221;450&#215;350&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text] Description: The smoke control dampers are intended to be installed in smoke and heat control systems, acting as a protection layer against the spreading of fire, temperature and smoke. During the normal operation of the system, the flap of the damper is in the open or closed position. In case&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":4563,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","dt_portfolio_category":[116],"dt_portfolio_tags":[],"class_list":["post-4562","dt_portfolio","type-dt_portfolio","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","dt_portfolio_category-en-fire-protection","dt_portfolio_category-116","description-off"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/klimacontra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/dt_portfolio\/4562","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/klimacontra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/dt_portfolio"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\